social_posts.post_text:
Why are you here? That was the only agenda item for our leadership meeting this week. With a moment to pause after another year full of challenges and progress, we challenged ourselves to reach for the core of why we were here @pressnapavalley and what drives each of us.
I was totally unprepared for the vulnerability, emotion and honesty that followed as each one shared their story. It is painfully clear that hospitality is a double-edged sword, full of passionate people pursuing excellence together, but all too often we are so focused on the goals we neglect and often mistreat the team that makes it happen every day. 
Our clear vision @pressnapavalley is to prove to ourselves that we can be different. That we can pursue excellence and achieve great things together without ruling through aggression, fear and intimidation. The negative, and long-lasting impact we can have on people through a culture that allows a demeaning and oppressive environment can’t be ignored.
It’s not easy, we all have our flaws and few, if any, of us have had a mentor that taught us what that looks like. Every day for me is a challenge to be different, to challenge the status quo, and to create a culture where each of us is looking out for each other from top to bottom. I struggle, and often I fail, but we keep pushing and we will continue to strive for this goal. 
It’s time to say goodbye to the Chef-Driven restaurant and pursue the Team-Driven restaurant that can be a beacon for others to follow. 
#hospitality #teamwork #honesty #accountability #change

Deeply saddened at the loss of Serge Veira, our dear friend and fellow leader of the @bocusedor community. In a world that can often be filled with competition and egos, Serge was a quiet leader full of hospitality and kindness. 
I am deeply thankful for every moment we spent together. The 10th anniversary dinner @sergevieiraofficiel , Cantal soup on the top of a remote mountain, foie gras and truffles in Sarlat and sandwiches in Chaudes-Aigues with Marie-Aude and your two beautiful kids. 
You have left us too soon, rest in peace my friend and may your legacy live on. ❤️ 
#sergeveira #bocusedor #community #💔

Such a pleasure to share this beautiful article written by @betsyandrews in @travelandleisure capturing the heart of @pressnapavalley 

« Press holds the world’s largest collection of Napa wines, many displayed in a glasses-in cellar, with labels dating back to the 1950s. From its advent as a down home steakhouse in 2007 to today, with its Michelin star and Wine Spectator Grand Award, this family-owned establishment in a light-filled space on the St. Helena Highway is dedicated to Napa, it’s history, and the ageability of its wines. »

The journey to get where we are today could not be possible without our incredible team and the support of our local community. 

Thank you @betsyandrews for capturing the essence of PRESS!

See link in bio for full article.

#napavalley #cuisine #michelinstar

Napa Valley Summer. Took me several years to adjust to the Napa Valley seasons, especially summer which starts much later than my East Coast roots due to the lower humidity and resulting cooler nights. 
But summer is worth the wait, as the farm brings in an abundance of fruits, vegetables and flowers at every stage of growth that we work hard to keep pace with! 
This dish of grilled kurobuta pork jowl from our friends @snakeriverfarms is the perfect canvas to showcase this summer bounty. Served with stone fruit and wax bean condiment, house cured nasturtium capers, wild ramps and fig leaf ajo blanco. 
📸 @troxphotos 

#napavalley #summerproduce #kurobuta #snakeriverfarms #michelinstar #finedining #pressrestaurant
